column1: #Text=The Atlanta Hawks defeated the host Orlando Magic , 111 - 92 , at Amway Center on Friday .
#Text=In a battle between two struggling teams , the Hawks were able to prevail with a huge road win .
#Text=In fact , there were 11 ties and 11 lead changes in total , with neither team leading by more than 11 points .
#Text=Defense was key for Atlanta , as they held Orlando to 43 percent from the field and 53 percent from three - point range .
#Text=Rebounding was a huge factor as well , with the Hawks recording 27 assists to 12 turnovers , while the Magic committed 17 turnovers to just 19 assists .
#Text=The Hawks ( 19 - 16 ) have now lost four of their last five games , as they continue to struggle .

column8: Annotators gave different explanations of why the team did not struggle, but meant the same thing (their record was improving)

column1: #Text=Dennis Schroder was the player of the game , as he tallied 18 points , six rebounds and seven assists on 7 - of - 13 shooting .
#Text=Dwight Howard recorded a double - double , totaling 13 points and 12 rebounds .
#Text=Kent Bazemore was the only other starter in double figures , as he totaled 17 points and four assists .
#Text=On deck for Atlanta is a home matchup against the New Orleans Pelicans on Saturday .
#Text=The Magic ( 16 - 21 ) have been struggling mightily recently , but this was a huge win .
#Text=Nikola Vucevic was the player of the game , as he collected 10 points , 12 rebounds and six assists .
#Text=Evan Fournier was second on the team , as he accrued 14 points , one rebound and one assist .
#Text=Nikola Vucevic recorded a double - double , totaling 10 points and 10 rebounds .
